Shares of the company, which have fallen 9.5% this year, were up 2.2% at $163.18 after the bell. Facebook said monthly active users in the first quarter rose to 2.2 billion, up 13% from a year earlier. Analysts on average had expected monthly active users of 2.2 billion, according to Thomson Reuters. Â Net income attributable to Facebook shareholders rose to $4.99 billion, or $1.69 per share, from $3.06 billion, or $1.04 per share, a year earlier. Analysts on average were expecting a profit of $1.35 per share. Total revenue rose 49% to $11.97 billion, above the analyst estimate of $11.41 billion. --Reuters--